trend_summary: Across the time-series the landscape remains dominantly rural, alternating between cropland and forest. Built-up footprints grow only marginally along main roads and village cores, keeping overall settlement sparse. Forest regrowth slightly enlarges wooded blocks in the north-east, while several fields consolidate into larger, paler parcels, hinting at intensified agriculture.
notable_changes: Minor expansion of village clusters and roadside ribbon development.
Noticeable consolidation of small fields into larger agricultural parcels, especially central-south.
Progressive regrowth and densification of forest patches in the north-east quadrant.
Selective logging creating fresh clear-cuts in western woodlots, later partially revegetated.
Slight improvement and straightening of the road network connecting hamlets.
